<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1261" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1261">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/437.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In a very satisfactory interview this afternoon with Ernesto Perusquia,
                            Director General of Stamp Tax Department, he stated that all questions
                            regarding payment of mining and other taxes by foreigners will be
                            equitably adjusted at the general stamp office in this city. Payments
                            for the entire Republic may be made here until further notice. The
                            general office will make proper explanation to the local offices.
                            Correspondence with the general office is recommended to all persons
                            interested. The proper address is Direccion General del Timbre, City of
                            Mexico.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>